                            <p>Some principles can be followed to make a flight with a pet to be safe or to have fewer troubles with the pet. Pet preparation for travel by air entails familiarizing the pet with the travel crate, researching airline requirements, and consulting your veterinarian about your pet’s fitness for flying.</p>
                            <p>Even concerning pets, every airline has limitations and policies as to the type of crate to use and whether the animals are to travel in the cabin or the cargo section. Therefore, the right choice and planning that should be made before the trip will contribute to a safe journey for you and your furry friend.</p>

                            <h2>Procedures for flight booking when traveling with a pet</h2>
                            <p>When flying with a pet, the procedures for <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/"><b>Flight ticket booking</b></a> generally involve the following steps:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Every airline is different when it comes to traveling with pets. Some aspects include the animal's size, charges, and the fact that the pet can travel inside the main cabin or as cargo.</li>
                                <li>Check out the official website of FaresMatch for charges that would be incurred for travelling with these animals. Check with the airline for these requirements, as they differ depending on whether your pet will be traveling in the cabin with you or in the belly hold of the plane.</li>
                                <li>It is recommended to prepare the necessary documents that may be required by the airline or country of destination, for example, health certificates or certificates of vaccination.</li>
                                <li>Make sure the pet is okay with traveling; have a correctly sized carrier according to the airline's specifications. Ensure your pet is fitted with identification collars/ tags and is comfortable with the travel cage/ crate.</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h2>Airlines that allow pets</h2>
                            <p>Most airlines today permit pet carriage, but there are variations in the way they do it. Here are some airlines known for accommodating pets:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><b>American Airlines</b>: Permits pets in the aircraft cabin, checked baggage or as shipments depending on their size and the particular destination.</li>
                                <li><b>Delta Air Lines</b>: The airline offers choices for carrying pets in the cabin, as check-in baggage, or in the belly of the plane.</li>
                                <li><b>Southwest Airlines</b>: Pets are permitted, but specific areas are to be avoided namely the cargo section.</li>
                                <li><b>United Airlines</b>: Provides pet travel in a cabin, as well as in the cargo hold.</li>
                                <li><b>Alaska Airlines</b>: Permits pets within the cabin, in the belly of the aircraft and at the aircraft door.</li>
                            </ul>

